            {
                "name": "Projects",
                "url": "/topics/projects"
            },
            {
                "name": "Idea",
                "url": "/topics/idea"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739354",
        "quote": "When you are interviewing someone, never let your camera person turn off the camera. The second you turn off the camera, they'll say the magic thing that you'd been looking for the whole interview. People want to relax after the performance is done. Don't be afraid of awkward silence. That is your friend.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Marshall Curry",
            "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739354"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Magic",
                "url": "/topics/magic"
            },
            {
                "name": "Interviewing",
                "url": "/topics/interviewing"
            },
            {
                "name": "Been",
                "url": "/topics/been"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739365",
        "quote": "In fiction film, there are so many trappings - money, glory, champagne and supermodels - that attract the wolves. But in documentary film, there's none of that, so the wolves stay away. The only people who make docs are people who are curious about other people and just like making documentaries.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Marshall Curry",
            "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739365"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Away",
                "url": "/topics/away"
            },
            {
                "name": "Fiction",
                "url": "/topics/fiction"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739362",
        "quote": "Of course no documentary is completely 'objective.' Every decision you make - who to interview, how to edit, where to hold the camera - imposes a point of view on the film.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Marshall Curry",
            "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739362"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Decision",
                "url": "/topics/decision"
            },
            {
                "name": "Film",
                "url": "/topics/film"
            },
            {
                "name": "Edit",
                "url": "/topics/edit"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739341",
        "quote": "If I were writing an article for the newspaper, it would be thesis statement, information, information, supporting arguments. That would be the setup. When I'm making a documentary, the pacing of the film and the way that you sort of switch from character to character - all of those are more about storytelling than straight journalism.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Marshall Curry",
            "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739341"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Storytelling",
                "url": "/topics/storytelling"
            },
            {
                "name": "Newspaper",
                "url": "/topics/newspaper"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/marshall_curry_739349",
        "quote": "My wife runs a non-profit that gives legal information online to victims of domestic violence.",
